We recommended that the Management, through the LCPC:
a. allocate 1% budget as required under the provisions of RA No. 9344 and DILG Memorandum Circular 2012-120 dated July 4, 2012;
b. facilitate the implementation of the programs, activities and projects of Republic Act 9344 known as the Juvenile Justice and Welfare Act of 2006 because the intended beneficiaries are the vulnerable members of the society.

We recommended that management:
a) Submit complete status report on the missing/un-presented properties; gather and account all unserviceable properties in a properly secured place and request for proper disposal;
b) create an inventory committee that will focus on the annual conduct of the physical inventory of all properties of the LGU and submit annual physical inventory report of the Property, Plant and Equipment;
c) ensure that all properties of the municipality issued to officer and employees shall be covered by PAR Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR), which shall be renewed every January of the third year after issue; and
d) require the Accounting Department to update the subsidiary ledgers of property plant and equipment to support the general ledger accounts to ensure completeness of the recorded amounts in the books of accounts; and
d. require the General Services Officer to prepare and maintain property cards and reconcile regularly with the accounting records.

